Keywords: CGE models, Migration, MONASH-MRF.
length: 27 pages
abstract: In analysing the effects of economic policy in a Federal system, such as 
    Australia, it is important to understand the interactions between the States 
    and Territories. In particular, given that there is free movement between 
    labour markets, to analyse economic policy it is important to understand the 
    factors influencing inter- regional migration. In this paper we use data from 
    1982 to 1996 to estimate a structural econometric model of inter-regional 
    migration. The results are then used to re-specify and calibrate the Computable 
    General Equilibrium model MONASH-MRF. This then provides a more detailed 
    picture of labour market responses when we subsequently simulate the response 
    of net interstate migration to changes in State Government spending.
